# VarInfoValueTypes.ParsingPrefix property

The prefix in the string representation of the type represented by this VarInfoValueType. A prefix is needed because some types, e.g double arrays, have a (variable) size in their name. So in this case, the type name is ParsingPrefix + size + ParsingPostfix.

```csharp
public string ParsingPrefix { get; }
```
